You are welcome to use and modify the GOLEM simulator.
See the README.md for details.

If you use GOLEM for your research, we would appreciate appropriate citation.
This includes a reference to the repository: (to add here)

And also a reference to the publication describing the theory and implementation of the GOLEM simulator:
Cacace, M. and Jacquey, A. B.: Flexible parallel implicit modelling of coupled thermal–hydraulic–mechanical processes in fractured rocks, Solid Earth, 8, 921-941, https://doi.org/10.5194/se-8-921-2017, 2017.
A BibTeX entry for LaTeX users is:

@Article{Golem,
AUTHOR = {Cacace, M. and Jacquey, A. B.},
TITLE = {Flexible parallel implicit modelling of coupled thermal--hydraulic--mechanical processes in fractured rocks},
